  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 44 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 680 mg
time required: 40 minutes
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Zest @lime{2} until you have 2 tsp zest; cut each into quarters. Mince or grate @garlic{4%cloves}. Trim any tough ends or strings from @green beans{12%ounce}. Roughly chop @peanuts{2%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle @vegetable oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add half the lime zest and cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add @jasmine rice{1%cup}, 1 3/4 cups water, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover, lower heat, and reduce to a gentle simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, place @soy sauce{4%tablespoon}, @cornstarch{2%teaspoon}, @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}, half the garlic, juice from two lime quarters, and @sugar{1%tablespoon} in a #small bowl{}. Whisk until smooth. Pat @chicken breasts{24%ounce} dry with a #paper towel{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken. Cook until browned, ~{4-6%minutes} per side. Pour sauce into pan and bring to a simmer. Cook until chicken is done and sauce thickens, about ~{2%minutes}, spooning sauce over chicken the whole time. Remove from heat. Stir in a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper. Transfer chicken and sauce to a #shallow dish{}.

Rinse or wipe pan clean. Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in same pan over medium-high heat. Add green beans and cook, tossing, until almost tender, ~{2-3%minutes}. Toss in peanuts, half the @sriracha{2%teaspoon}, all of the remaining garlic, and @butter{1%tablespoon}. Cook, tossing, until peanuts are lightly toasted, ~{1-3%minutes}. Remove from heat and stir in a squeeze of lime juice. Season with salt and pepper.

> Add remaining sriracha for extra heat.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}, then stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lime juice, and a pinch of salt and pepper. Divide rice and green beans between plates. Arrange chicken over rice, drizzling over any extra sauce. Garnish with remaining lime zest. Serve with lime quarters on the side.